law.text:
The Plan shall contain recommendations for the most desirable general pattern of land use in the State. The recommendations shall be based on the best available information concerning:
environmental and natural factors, including climate, soil and underground conditions, topography, and water sources and bodies of water;
present and prospective economic bases of the State;
water and sewerage facilities;
trends of industrial, population, or other developments;
habits and standards of life of the people of the State; and
the relation of land use in the State to land use in adjoining areas.
